00:18:59,890 --> 00:19:02,835
It's a scary thing, Pete.
My heart's in my throat.

236
00:19:02,935 --> 00:19:05,629
Got a good doctor?
- Supposed to be the best in the country.

237
00:19:05,729 --> 00:19:07,756
OK.
Then everything's gonna be all right.

238
00:19:07,856 --> 00:19:11,510
These guys today can perform miracles.
There's nothing they can't do, OK, Buddy?

239
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:13,345
Yeah.
- Everything's gonna be all right. All right?

240
00:19:13,445 --> 00:19:16,390
Yeah.
- All right, kid? Get outta here.

241
00:19:16,490 --> 00:19:18,267
Bring it out here
and let me have a look at it.

242
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:20,369
Pete.

243
00:19:20,619 --> 00:19:23,622
Yeah.
- That guy's here again.

244
00:19:23,747 --> 00:19:27,062
Says he's not leaving till he sees you.

245
00:19:27,292 --> 00:19:30,352
Thanks.
- Way to go, Mario.

246
00:19:30,629 --> 00:19:33,615
I don't understand, Pete.
Why's everything changed around here?

247
00:19:33,715 --> 00:19:38,162
Nothing's changed, believe me.
It's just a lot of bullshit with the league.

248
00:19:38,262 --> 00:19:41,665
They don't want any nonbaseball people
on the field, in the clubhouse.

249
00:19:41,765 --> 00:19:44,543
All this time, it's never been a problem.
- Well, it is now.

250
00:19:44,643 --> 00:19:48,589
What about Paulie?
Why is it OK for him all of a sudden?

251
00:19:48,689 --> 00:19:53,010
Look, I'm working on this.
Just give it a little time.

252
00:19:53,110 --> 00:19:57,556
Gio, come on. Have I ever let you down,
Gio? Have I ever let you down?

253
00:19:57,656 --> 00:20:00,659
Have I ever let you down?

254
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:04,989
I miss you, man.
Just hanging out, the two of us.

255
00:20:07,666 --> 00:20:10,669
Come on.
No, come on.

256
00:20:10,704 --> 00:20:11,987
Sorry.

257
00:20:12,087 --> 00:20:14,173
Hey.
Come on.

258
00:20:18,093 --> 00:20:20,898
Hey, who's better than us, right?

259
00:20:20,971 --> 00:20:22,971
Nobody.

260
00:20:26,101 --> 00:20:28,145
I gotta...

261
00:20:28,645 --> 00:20:31,960
I'll see you soon, man.
- Yeah. Go on.

262
00:20:54,338 --> 00:20:56,281
There's nothing more beautiful.

263
00:20:56,381 --> 00:20:58,784
A ballpark a couple of hours
before game time is close,

264
00:20:58,884 --> 00:21:01,453
but you don't get
that earthy smell like this.

265
00:21:01,553 --> 00:21:05,833
I think I'd come to the track
even if I couldn't bet the ponies.

266
00:21:05,933 --> 00:21:10,098
You know, I never even
placed a bet before we met.

267
00:21:10,312 --> 00:21:12,131
Really?
- Yeah.

268
00:21:12,231 --> 00:21:16,427
How'd you manage that?
- It just never occurred to me.

269
00:21:16,527 --> 00:21:20,055
I don't think it's never
not occurred to me.

270
00:21:20,155 --> 00:21:24,977
It's like when you feel that solid crack,
and you know you got a stand-up double.

271
00:21:25,077 --> 00:21:27,396
You're rounding first base
and you watch that outfielder.

272
00:21:27,496 --> 00:21:28,939
Now it's all a matter of odds.

273
00:21:29,039 --> 00:21:32,234
What are the chances he's gonna make
a perfect throw if you head for third base?

274
00:21:32,334 --> 00:21:36,074
Is he even thinking third?
That's the gamble.

275
00:21:36,213 --> 00:21:39,199
Can you stretch a stand-up double
into a triple?

276
00:21:39,299 --> 00:21:41,385
Can you beat the odds?

277
00:21:42,261 --> 00:21:46,039
It takes a special kind of person
to have that kind of confidence.

278
00:21:46,139 --> 00:21:50,219
No. You just have to be willing
to be thrown out.

279
00:21:51,645 --> 00:21:54,882
You could play it safe.
Stop at second base.

280
00:21:54,982 --> 00:21:57,025
Most guys do.

281
00:21:58,235 --> 00:22:01,263
You know, I don't think a lot of people
really know you, Pete.

282
00:22:01,363 --> 00:22:03,015
What?

283
00:22:03,115 --> 00:22:07,195
I don't think a lot of people...
- I heard you.

284
00:22:07,327 --> 00:22:11,577
Hey. Here comes Ronnie.
Play it cool with this guy.

285
00:22:11,915 --> 00:22:14,210
Hey, Ronnie.
- Who's this?

286
00:22:14,293 --> 00:22:18,030
The guy I told you about. My buddy Paulie
from Cincinnati. He's good people.

287
00:22:18,130 --> 00:22:21,133
Says who?
- Says me. Pete Rose.

288
00:22:22,759 --> 00:22:24,536
I don't really like meeting new people.

289
00:22:24,636 --> 00:22:28,415
But out of respect for Pete here
I'm gonna make an exception in your case.

290
00:22:28,515 --> 00:22:32,170
Take a walk with me,
Paulie from Cincinnati.

291
00:22:44,656 --> 00:22:47,976
You been a friend of Pete's long?
- Not really that long,

292
00:22:48,076 --> 00:22:52,898
but we pretty much grew up in the same
area, so it's kinda like we go back...

293
00:22:52,998 --> 00:22:55,317
What's that mean? 'Kinda like? '
- Uh...

294
00:22:55,417 --> 00:22:58,612
Why you so nervous, Paul?
What? Am I terrifying?

295
00:22:58,712 --> 00:23:02,877
I'm just not really sure
what we're talking about.

296
00:23:03,133 --> 00:23:06,453
I'm a cautious man. I believe in looking
both ways before I cross the street.

297
00:23:06,553 --> 00:23:09,498
You a gambling man, Paul?
- Now and then.

298
00:23:09,598 --> 00:23:12,960
Pete's a gambling man.
Has a real passion for it.

299
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:15,379
Which, for a guy in his position,
is not necessarily a good thing.

300
00:23:15,479 --> 00:23:18,757
That's where you would come in.
- I'm a little lost.

301
00:23:18,857 --> 00:23:22,261
You're gonna phone Pete's picks into me.
I'm gonna relay that action to New York.

302
00:23:22,361 --> 00:23:25,431
You see how it works now?
Everyone's clean, once removed.

303
00:23:25,531 --> 00:23:27,933
L- I think I should talk to Pete about...

304
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:31,353
Pete already talked to me about it.
Now I'm talking to you.

305
00:23:31,453 --> 00:23:36,128
You can't handle the weight,
we'll find someone who can.

306
00:23:37,793 --> 00:23:39,878
I can handle it.

307
00:23:41,797 --> 00:23:43,991
Monday after weekend's game
is settle-up time.

308
00:23:44,091 --> 00:23:46,952
Pete gets a little forgetful.
lets things slide.

309
00:23:47,052 --> 00:23:50,164
It is now part of your job
to make sure that don't happen.

310
00:23:50,264 --> 00:23:52,307
Nice meeting you, Paul.

311
00:24:06,405 --> 00:24:08,307
All right. I'll see you next week.
Thanks for coming.

312
00:24:08,407 --> 00:24:11,602
Hey, it's Tommy Helms.
- Good game. Good game.

313
00:24:11,702 --> 00:24:14,146
You happy, Tommy?
- Yeah, I'm happy. That's the way to do it.

314
00:24:14,246 --> 00:24:18,581
Sorry about that.
- Bad break. It'll be all right.

315
00:24:20,085 --> 00:24:23,489
My cut's 75 percent, right?
- Forget about it. This is like stealing.

316
00:24:23,589 --> 00:24:26,479
Just ask Pete.
- OK, Mikey. Cool.

317
00:24:29,094 --> 00:24:32,998
When we talk baseball Cincinnati,
there's only one team to talk about.

318
00:24:33,098 --> 00:24:35,098
NBA.

319
00:24:36,768 --> 00:24:37,878
Hey, Pete.
- Hey.

320
00:24:37,978 --> 00:24:43,050
Can I have a second?
Got a kid needs some help on the infield.

321
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:46,040
Give us a minute, will you, Tommy?

322
00:24:49,031 --> 00:24:51,074
Tommy.
You deal with it.

323
00:24:52,326 --> 00:24:56,522
That's why I hired you.
You're the best. Only the best.

324
00:24:56,622 --> 00:24:58,357
OK.
All right.

325
00:24:58,457 --> 00:25:00,459
Hey, Doug.
- Tommy.

326
00:25:03,003 --> 00:25:05,047
We need to talk, Pete.

327
00:25:06,089 --> 00:25:08,133
In private.

328
00:25:08,592 --> 00:25:10,592
Hey.

329
00:25:21,939 --> 00:25:26,104
We got a problem.
- Not from where I'm standing.

330
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:29,221
I'm talking about the nonbaseball
personnel in the clubhouse.

331
00:25:29,321 --> 00:25:31,723
You know it's against regulations.

332
00:25:31,823 --> 00:25:34,852
You came down here to mess with me
over that rinky-dink rule?

333
00:25:34,952 --> 00:25:36,937
The commissioner
doesn't see it that way.

334
00:25:37,037 --> 00:25:40,274
Well then, have him call me
and we'll talk about it.

335
00:25:40,374 --> 00:25:43,094
My friends ain't hurting nobody.

336
00:25:43,502 --> 00:25:47,156
I don't make the rules,
but it's my job to enforce them,

337
00:25:47,256 --> 00:25:52,035
and from here on out, you're gonna
stick to them like everyone else.

338
00:25:52,135 --> 00:25:54,685
Get out of my office.
- What?

339
00:25:54,972 --> 00:25:59,293
Get out... You heard me loud and clear.
We're done here.

340
00:25:59,393 --> 00:26:01,628
This is going straight to Marge.
- Hey.

341
00:26:01,728 --> 00:26:03,839
You think the owner of this damned team's
gonna side with you?

342
00:26:03,939 --> 00:26:06,925
I put the asses on all those seats
every night. Not you.

343
00:26:07,025 --> 00:26:10,220
Not some bozo in a monkey suit.
- Take a good look in the mirror, Rose.

344
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:13,599
You're just another 45-year-old has-been
managing a baseball team.

345
00:26:13,699 --> 00:26:18,544
Nothing more or less.
- Hey, Doug. Let's leave. Come on.

346
00:26:27,087 --> 00:26:30,282
The commissioner's a stickler
for the nonbaseball personnel rule.

347
00:26:30,382 --> 00:26:32,743
You know that.
- I didn't appreciate being lectured.

348
00:26:32,843 --> 00:26:35,579
Doug has a job to do,
and I'm the one who pays him to do it.

349
00:26:35,679 --> 00:26:36,789
I'll stick by the rules, Marge.

350
00:26:36,889 --> 00:26:39,708
I don't pay him to look the other way.
- No problem. OK.

351
00:26:39,808 --> 00:26:42,294
We have a good team this year.
- Flattery, Marge, will get you everywhere.

352
00:26:42,394 --> 00:26:45,794
But outside distractions, we don't need.

353
00:26:46,023 --> 00:26:50,594
Now, I chose you to manage this team
because you're a winner.

354
00:26:50,694 --> 00:26:52,096
I can say in all honesty...

355
00:26:52,196 --> 00:26:55,849
that no single man has ever
meant as much to the city of Cincinnati.

356
00:26:55,949 --> 00:26:57,976
And here I thought
I was gonna get chewed out.

357
00:26:58,076 --> 00:27:00,626
I'm making a point here, Pete.

358
00:27:00,746 --> 00:27:03,816
Can I count on you
to do the right thing?

359
00:27:03,916 --> 00:27:06,735
Ms. Schott. That call...
- Yes. Yep.

360
00:27:06,835 --> 00:27:09,321
I'll be right back.
- Margie, put it out of your mind.

361
00:27:09,421 --> 00:27:11,281
Pete Rose won't let you
or the Reds down.

362
00:27:11,381 --> 00:27:14,271
I'm as happy as hell to hear that.

363
00:27:38,951 --> 00:27:40,951
Paulie.

364
00:27:42,246 --> 00:27:44,289
Here.
You know.

365
00:27:50,337 --> 00:27:53,340
Cleveland, plus nine.

366
00:27:53,549 --> 00:27:56,593
Utah, minus five.

367
00:27:57,135 --> 00:27:59,221
Boston, minus two.

368
00:28:00,138 --> 00:28:02,224
LA, minus fifteen.

369
00:28:03,225 --> 00:28:06,228
All right.
Yep.

370
00:28:06,603 --> 00:28:09,606
Sacramento, minus five.

371
00:28:09,731 --> 00:28:11,775
Uh-huh.

372
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:15,554
Let's go.
Come on on the inside, baby, let's go.

373
00:28:15,654 --> 00:28:17,014
Come on, come on.

374
00:28:17,114 --> 00:28:19,157
No. No. No.

375
00:28:19,908 --> 00:28:22,953
Paul, no.
I gotta stop losing.

376
00:28:37,259 --> 00:28:39,259
Hello.
This is Paul.

377
00:28:39,344 --> 00:28:41,413
...needs at least a point.

378
00:28:41,513 --> 00:28:43,582
...is not the man you want to shoot.

379
00:28:43,682 --> 00:28:46,293
Gets the ball out off the hand. No.

380
00:28:46,393 --> 00:28:49,538
They foul him with two seconds to go.

381
00:29:04,703 --> 00:29:05,729
Hello.

382
00:29:05,829 --> 00:29:09,858
If I don't get my money by week's
end, you're gonna have big problems.

383
00:29:09,958 --> 00:29:10,943
Ron?

384
00:29:11,043 --> 00:29:13,195
You're responsible,
not the other guy.

385
00:29:13,295 --> 00:29:16,907
I break your friggin' legs,
no one will give a shit.

386
00:29:17,007 --> 00:29:20,577
That's crazy.
- That's reality, jerk off.

387
00:29:21,303 --> 00:29:23,347
Get my money.

388
00:29:29,895 --> 00:29:31,939
Who was that?

389
00:29:33,065 --> 00:29:35,065
Nobody.

390
00:29:35,901 --> 00:29:39,556
Baby, who was that?
You're white as a sheet.

391
00:29:40,072 --> 00:29:42,115
I'm fine. I'm fine.

392
00:29:44,576 --> 00:29:47,563
Sure you know what you're doing?
- Yeah.

393
00:29:47,663 --> 00:29:49,706
Go back to sleep.

394
00:29:59,716 --> 00:30:02,369
Come on, let me give you
the five-cent tour. That's what Pete calls it.

395
00:30:02,469 --> 00:30:05,497
Yeah, more like
the 50 million-dollar tour.

396
00:30:05,597 --> 00:30:08,147
Not quite.
We're working on it.

397
00:30:09,184 --> 00:30:12,045
Ron's not messing around, Pete.
He threatened me.

398
00:30:12,145 --> 00:30:16,842
These guys are all the same. Bums.
A bunch of crybabies. Tell him to wait.

399
00:30:16,942 --> 00:30:19,236
You tell him.

400
00:30:20,445 --> 00:30:23,932
The whole idea of you being the
middleman is that I stay outside of the loop.

401
00:30:24,032 --> 00:30:27,019
I thought you understood that.
- I do.

402
00:30:27,119 --> 00:30:29,188
But you've put me
in a situation here, Pete.

403
00:30:29,288 --> 00:30:33,442
I mean, I can't have people
calling my house in the middle of the night...

404
00:30:33,542 --> 00:30:37,321
saying they're gonna hurt me
unless you make good.

405
00:30:37,421 --> 00:30:41,033
It's betting, Pete. If you win, they pay.
If you lose, you pay.

406
00:30:41,133 --> 00:30:43,869
You're explaining how it works to me?
- No. I...

407
00:30:43,969 --> 00:30:46,080
You know what? To hell with it.
I'll find someone else.

408
00:30:46,180 --> 00:30:48,332
I figured I could rely on you,
you were my friend, but I was wrong.

409
00:30:48,432 --> 00:30:50,042
No, you're not wrong.
- I was wrong.

410
00:30:50,142 --> 00:30:52,352
I'm your guy.

411
00:30:52,394 --> 00:30:56,729
Just let me have a little something
to hold Ron off.

412
00:30:58,358 --> 00:31:01,762
Guy's got a lot of balls
calling my pal up in the middle of the night.

413
00:31:01,862 --> 00:31:04,556
Maybe I'll call him up.
Threaten to have his ass thrown in jail.

414
00:31:04,656 --> 00:31:07,392
No. No.
He didn't mean anything by it.

415
00:31:07,492 --> 00:31:09,978
I mean,
this'll put his mind right at ease.

416
00:31:10,078 --> 00:31:13,732
These guys don't give a damn about me.
The cops, they all love Pete Rose.

417
00:31:13,832 --> 00:31:16,693
It's scumbags like Ron Delaplane
they wanna throw in jail.

418
00:31:16,793 --> 00:31:20,072
Now, he ought to keep that in mind
next time he wants to pick up a phone.

419
00:31:20,172 --> 00:31:23,659
You know what? Forget I said it.
It's water under the bridge.

420
00:31:23,759 --> 00:31:26,678
OK. So, um...

421
00:31:26,762 --> 00:31:29,289
What's the line on the Celtics tonight?

422
00:31:29,389 --> 00:31:30,416
Huh?

423
00:31:30,516 --> 00:31:31,708
I'll find out.
- Good.

424
00:31:31,808 --> 00:31:35,587
OK. Be quick about it. The game starts
at 7:30, and I want to get ten dimes on it.

425
00:31:35,687 --> 00:31:38,662
Ten?
- Ten. What? I got a stutter?

426
00:31:39,483 --> 00:31:43,262
Hey. How do you get a blonde
to laugh on a Wednesday?

427
00:31:43,362 --> 00:31:45,864
Tell her a joke on Monday.

428
00:31:46,949 --> 00:31:51,787
Hey. Get down on the Lakers,
too. That one's a lock.

429
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:56,817
They're all a lock until the game's over.
- Oh, Paul, come on.

430
00:31:56,917 --> 00:31:58,986
You know I can't watch a game
unless I got something riding on it.

431
00:31:59,086 --> 00:32:02,061
I ain't got no hobbies.
It's sports.

432
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:05,634
When I was a boy,
before I went to bed,

433
00:32:05,717 --> 00:32:08,370
my old man made me take 100 swings
from the left, 100 from the right.

434
00:32:08,470 --> 00:32:12,875
You know why? He knew if I didn't make it
in baseball, I wasn't going nowhere.

435
00:32:12,975 --> 00:32:17,395
That's the way it's always been.
It's all or nothing.

436
00:32:18,146 --> 00:32:21,358
We'll get 'em tonight, Pete.
- OK.

437
00:32:21,441 --> 00:32:23,441
Thanks.

438
00:32:24,736 --> 00:32:27,639
Right there, a fountain. With flowers.
- Oh, I want a fountain.

439
00:32:27,739 --> 00:32:29,808
Katarina, honey, we have to go.

440
00:32:29,908 --> 00:32:31,351
Oh. Is everything all right?
- Yeah.

441
00:32:31,451 --> 00:32:34,730
Hi. Sorry, Carol. Nice to see you.
- Hi, Paulie. It's OK. Good to see you, too.

442
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:36,982
Uh... Thank you.
- All right.

443
00:32:37,082 --> 00:32:39,860
Let's have lunch next week. Call me.
- OK. Bye.

444
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,960
Bye.

445
00:32:48,927 --> 00:32:51,722
There you go.

446
00:32:55,684 --> 00:32:57,711
Your boss should only bet
on things he knows.

447
00:32:57,811 --> 00:32:58,670
Huh?

448
00:32:58,770 --> 00:33:02,716
I say something, you say 'huh? '
What are you? Deaf?

449
00:33:02,816 --> 00:33:05,010
You want Pete to bet on baseball?

450
00:33:05,110 --> 00:33:07,054
He don't manage
a hockey team, Einstein.

451
00:33:07,154 --> 00:33:08,680
So what can I get ya?
- Coffee, black.

452
00:33:08,780 --> 00:33:10,780
OK.

453
00:33:12,492 --> 00:33:15,042
We'll have the rest next week.

454
00:33:16,955 --> 00:33:22,277
Pete won't cross that line. It's something
he'd never do. Bet on his own sport.

455
00:33:22,377 --> 00:33:26,712
You're so dumb,
you shouldn't be allowed to breathe.

456
00:33:27,257 --> 00:33:30,997
You find that amusing?
- No, of course not.

457
00:33:31,094 --> 00:33:32,579
Then why are you laughing, goof?

458
00:33:32,679 --> 00:33:36,334
I guess it made me nervous,
you saying that.

459
00:33:36,391 --> 00:33:38,560
Come here.
Come here.

460
00:33:41,313 --> 00:33:43,924
Let me explain something to you, Paul.

461
00:33:44,024 --> 00:33:48,095
You place bets with me for Pete.
I take that action, I lay it off in New York.

462
00:33:48,195 --> 00:33:52,057
When Pete doesn't pay me, I gotta come
up with his losses outta my own pocket.

463
00:33:52,157 --> 00:33:56,228
If I don't pay them, I'm outta business,
and that's the least of my problems.

464
00:33:56,328 --> 00:34:00,774
