I mean, after all, it's just a big TV.

549
00:40:40,941 --> 00:40:43,469
It's no hassle to us.
It's more of a fan thing.

550
00:40:43,569 --> 00:40:45,721
Well, I hope they don't take long
in getting it fixed.

551
00:40:45,821 --> 00:40:47,821
Yeah.

552
00:40:56,915 --> 00:40:59,209
Something else?
- Yeah.

553
00:41:03,422 --> 00:41:07,743
How long we known each other, Pete?
Twenty, twenty-five years?

554
00:41:07,843 --> 00:41:10,245
Give or take.
- Yeah. All that time.

555
00:41:10,345 --> 00:41:15,459
We've seen a lot of players come and go,
huh? Some good, some not so good.

556
00:41:15,559 --> 00:41:17,002
But what always broke my heart...

557
00:41:17,102 --> 00:41:20,964
was when one of the real greats
did something - you know -...

558
00:41:21,064 --> 00:41:25,986
got involved in something
that tarnished their reputation.

559
00:41:27,321 --> 00:41:30,516
Are you fishing for something, Tom?
- Nah.

560
00:41:30,616 --> 00:41:32,951
Tom. No.

561
00:41:39,499 --> 00:41:42,194
I got nothing but respect for you, Pete.

562
00:41:42,294 --> 00:41:44,922
Just wanted you to know that.

563
00:41:45,881 --> 00:41:48,258
Tom.
- Yeah?

564
00:41:51,678 --> 00:41:54,206
What do you say we go see
those big repairmen, get that TV fixed?

565
00:41:54,306 --> 00:41:58,435
All right. Come on. Let's go.

566
00:42:14,368 --> 00:42:16,368
Stee.

567
00:42:25,337 --> 00:42:27,337
Let's go, Dave.

568
00:42:29,007 --> 00:42:31,343
OK. OK.
Thank you.

569
00:42:45,482 --> 00:42:47,482
Stee.

570
00:42:56,743 --> 00:42:58,743
You're out.

571
00:43:17,514 --> 00:43:20,250
No one's down here.
This guy's way left.

572
00:43:20,350 --> 00:43:24,685
That's a foul.
- Foul. Going the other way.

573
00:43:25,272 --> 00:43:28,801
Oh. Nice shot, nice shot.
Now you gotta get up.

574
00:43:28,901 --> 00:43:32,988
Oh, damn.
Son of a...

575
00:43:37,117 --> 00:43:39,369
How much this time?

576
00:43:42,414 --> 00:43:44,499
I'm going to bed.

577
00:43:44,917 --> 00:43:48,420
Hey, where you been, baby?
- Out.

578
00:43:51,131 --> 00:43:53,258
Get 'em next time.

579
00:43:53,342 --> 00:43:55,344
Why not?

580
00:43:57,221 --> 00:43:59,456
We're gonna go shopping.
You like shopping, right?

581
00:43:59,556 --> 00:44:05,421
Come on, help me open the door.
There you go. We're gonna go shopping.

582
00:44:08,565 --> 00:44:10,984
Yeah, Dada.
- Dada.

583
00:44:13,153 --> 00:44:15,013
Hello.

584
00:44:15,113 --> 00:44:18,684
Hey, what kind of a way is that to start off
a conversation? 'I want my money. '

585
00:44:18,784 --> 00:44:23,021
It's Ronnie. Huh? Oh look.
No, no, no, no. You've got it all wrong here.

586
00:44:23,121 --> 00:44:24,857
It's Paulie.

587
00:44:24,957 --> 00:44:26,957
Yeah, Janszen.

588
00:44:26,959 --> 00:44:29,653
He's been placing all kinds of crazy bets
all over town and laying them off on me.

589
00:44:29,753 --> 00:44:31,739
I think he's got
a screw loose or something.

590
00:44:31,839 --> 00:44:35,242
Oh, no. I wouldn't mess with him.
He's like 110 percent crazy, believe me.

591
00:44:35,342 --> 00:44:40,264
I seen him almost kill a guy once.
Yeah... He hung up.

592
00:44:40,347 --> 00:44:43,584
Do you know what you just did?
The position you just put me in?

593
00:44:43,684 --> 00:44:45,461
He's scared shitless.
What are you worried about?

594
00:44:45,561 --> 00:44:47,629
Jeez, Pete.
That guy's connected.

595
00:44:47,729 --> 00:44:50,007
He's like in the Mafia or something.
- Mafia?

596
00:44:50,107 --> 00:44:52,593
That's movie crap.
These bums are a bunch of pansies.

597
00:44:52,693 --> 00:44:56,764
No. I've seen the look in Ronnie's eye,
you know? He means business.

598
00:44:56,864 --> 00:44:59,683
What? Are you a pussy?
Are you a big pussy, Paulie?

599
00:44:59,783 --> 00:45:02,077
All show and no go?

600
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:03,562
Hm?

601
00:45:03,662 --> 00:45:05,814
Pete,
why are you talking to me like that?

602
00:45:05,914 --> 00:45:09,401
I've been dealing with scum
like Ron Delaplane my whole life, all right?

603
00:45:09,501 --> 00:45:12,529
It's his job to threaten me.
You know, say he'll cut me off.

604
00:45:12,629 --> 00:45:15,115
But the thing is, what are these jerks
gonna do without guys like me?

605
00:45:15,215 --> 00:45:18,660
I'm their bread and butter.
I'm the reason he's in business, see?

606
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:20,454
He's gonna get his money.
I just wanna make him sweat...

607
00:45:20,554 --> 00:45:23,165
and make him
remember who's the boss.

608
00:45:23,265 --> 00:45:25,265
See?

609
00:45:28,270 --> 00:45:31,215
Come on, Paulie.
Who's better than us, huh?

610
00:45:31,315 --> 00:45:33,734
Tell me who.

611
00:45:33,775 --> 00:45:36,070
Yo, buddy.
I'm waiting here.

612
00:45:40,657 --> 00:45:42,657
All right.

613
00:46:00,969 --> 00:46:03,138
Safe.

614
00:46:46,139 --> 00:46:50,252
He makes millions every year.
- Just for a few weeks. His money's tied up.

615
00:46:50,352 --> 00:46:52,546
Carol's on him like a hawk.
- Oh, like she doesn't have reason to.

616
00:46:52,646 --> 00:46:54,339
Why do you think
he blew off Gio, huh?

617
00:46:54,439 --> 00:46:56,675
I told you I don't want you talking to him.
- Pete owes him a fortune.

618
00:46:56,775 --> 00:46:58,177
Gio's a full-of-shit druggie.

619
00:46:58,277 --> 00:47:02,347
Maybe he got sick of being stepped on.
- He's my best friend in the world.

620
00:47:02,447 --> 00:47:06,685
Maybe he'd had enough of Pete's lies.
- How could you even think he'd stiff me?

621
00:47:06,785 --> 00:47:09,855
I don't have your faith in human nature.

622
00:47:09,955 --> 00:47:12,357
Let's not talk about this ever again.

623
00:47:12,457 --> 00:47:15,262
I hope we don't have a reason to.

624
00:47:23,594 --> 00:47:26,747
The memorabilia biz
not so hot these days?

625
00:47:26,847 --> 00:47:30,209
Just running a little short.
You know how it is.

626
00:47:30,309 --> 00:47:32,044
Look,
you don't gotta play cute with me.

627
00:47:32,144 --> 00:47:35,255
That jerk burned me for 75 Gs
on that piece-of-shit Beamer of his.

628
00:47:35,355 --> 00:47:37,758
Frigging engine was scrap metal.

629
00:47:37,858 --> 00:47:40,385
You really think Pete knew that?

630
00:47:40,485 --> 00:47:43,555
I think number 14
looks out for number one, is what I think.

631
00:47:43,655 --> 00:47:45,949
Well, don't we all?

632
00:47:46,867 --> 00:47:49,927
What have you got here? 50?
- Yeah.

633
00:47:52,497 --> 00:47:56,360
Number 14's into everybody.
You know that, right?

634
00:47:56,460 --> 00:47:58,712
Me, Gio, Mike.

635
00:47:59,421 --> 00:48:03,242
The thing is, when you're Pete Rose,
you don't gotta pay schmucks like us back.

636
00:48:03,342 --> 00:48:07,413
'Cause we're just mortals. And he's
the guy who broke Ty Cobb's record.

637
00:48:07,513 --> 00:48:10,624
That's the difference right there,
Steng, see?

638
00:48:10,724 --> 00:48:16,589
I don't consider myself a schmuck.
And Pete doesn't treat me like one.

639
00:48:18,690 --> 00:48:23,195
Yeah, when I was a kid
I believed in fairy tales, too.

640
00:49:23,589 --> 00:49:26,492
Did you ever settle up
with you know who?

641
00:49:26,592 --> 00:49:29,567
No.
He still owes me about 12 grand.

642
00:49:30,262 --> 00:49:33,492
So, how much did he pay you?
- Nothing.

643
00:49:33,557 --> 00:49:35,876
He signed a bunch of autographs for me,
you know, to sell.

644
00:49:35,976 --> 00:49:40,798
