Is that it?

690
00:52:31,777 --> 00:52:34,613
No.
No, of course not.

691
00:52:34,696 --> 00:52:38,100
Pete, you know I'd do anything for you.
I'd go to the wall.

692
00:52:38,200 --> 00:52:41,203
I just...
I need to get away from...

693
00:52:41,245 --> 00:52:44,189
I need to get away
from the other stuff, you know?

694
00:52:44,289 --> 00:52:46,375
The betting.

695
00:52:46,416 --> 00:52:50,337
It's got me like I can't think straight.

696
00:52:54,049 --> 00:52:57,911
I got you something.
You probably don't want it now.

697
00:52:58,011 --> 00:53:00,889
Look at the back.

698
00:53:05,853 --> 00:53:09,465
Paulie, my number 1 fan and friend.
Pete Rose.

699
00:53:09,565 --> 00:53:11,467
Take it back if you want.
Get something else.

700
00:53:11,567 --> 00:53:15,647
The jeweler I got it from,
he's a friend of mine.

701
00:53:16,405 --> 00:53:18,740
I wouldn't.

702
00:53:19,908 --> 00:53:22,628
I wouldn't trade it for my life.

703
00:53:23,662 --> 00:53:25,662
Thanks.

704
00:53:27,457 --> 00:53:30,736
Hey, you know what we need? We need
a night on the town, just you and me.

705
00:53:30,836 --> 00:53:36,241
And some fresh tail. What do you say
you come with me to LA this weekend?

706
00:53:36,341 --> 00:53:37,910
I'm... I...

707
00:53:38,010 --> 00:53:41,038
It sounds great, but Katarina and all...

708
00:53:41,138 --> 00:53:42,873
Oh, yeah.

709
00:53:42,973 --> 00:53:47,019
OK, here.
Put it on. See if it fits.

710
00:53:47,060 --> 00:53:49,213
You can see the moon
and all of its quarters.

711
00:53:49,313 --> 00:53:51,924
This is the kind the astronauts wear,
this model.

712
00:53:52,024 --> 00:53:55,469
Come on, buddy.
Katarina's gotta get used to it.

713
00:53:55,569 --> 00:53:57,596
You're on the road with me - Pete Rose.

714
00:53:57,696 --> 00:54:01,521
You don't hear Carol complaining,
now, do you?

715
00:54:02,075 --> 00:54:06,438
Hey, baby. I got the Roller all shined
and polished for you. Where you going?

716
00:54:06,538 --> 00:54:08,232
Egypt.

717
00:54:08,332 --> 00:54:11,084
Bring me back a mummy.

718
00:54:15,672 --> 00:54:21,622
You don't think she heard?
- Nah, it's just her goofy sense of humor.

719
00:54:21,970 --> 00:54:23,914
Come on.
Get the stick out of your ass.

720
00:54:24,014 --> 00:54:26,792
All work and no play,
you know, whatever that is.

721
00:54:26,892 --> 00:54:30,103
Who's better than us?
Tell me who.

722
00:54:30,145 --> 00:54:34,191
Nobody.
- That's right, pal. Nobody.

723
00:54:34,233 --> 00:54:36,233
Nobody.

724
00:54:42,824 --> 00:54:44,826
Thank you.

725
00:54:50,249 --> 00:54:54,586
No.
- Yes. You better come here.

726
00:54:54,628 --> 00:54:56,628
Gotcha.

727
00:55:02,511 --> 00:55:05,414
Open the door.
- It's my wife.

728
00:55:05,514 --> 00:55:08,517
I said open the door, Pete.

729
00:55:09,518 --> 00:55:11,378
Let me in right now.

730
00:55:11,478 --> 00:55:14,481
Right now.
- Coming.

731
00:55:14,606 --> 00:55:17,676
Open the door.
I hear you in there. Let me in right now.

732
00:55:17,776 --> 00:55:21,363
OK.
- Open this damn door.

733
00:55:21,446 --> 00:55:25,267
Who is it? I'm coming.
- Open the damn door. Let me in.

734
00:55:25,367 --> 00:55:27,394
Carol.
What are you doing in LA, huh?

735
00:55:27,494 --> 00:55:30,539
Who is it, huh?
- Carol?

736
00:55:30,622 --> 00:55:33,041
W- What are you looking for?

737
00:55:33,125 --> 00:55:35,194
Who's next door?
- Paul. You know that.

738
00:55:35,294 --> 00:55:37,462
Yeah, Paul?

739
00:55:42,968 --> 00:55:45,688
Katarina would love to see this.

740
00:55:45,929 --> 00:55:48,932
Carol, please.

741
00:55:49,850 --> 00:55:53,045
I don't wanna see him.
I don't wanna hear his voice on our phone...

742
00:55:53,145 --> 00:55:56,715
or see him within a mile of a ballpark or
anywhere else you might be for that matter.

743
00:55:56,815 --> 00:56:00,969
That guy, he is bad news.
He's been nothing but since you met him.

744
00:56:01,069 --> 00:56:05,682
This stuff, and this gambling,
it has taken us to a new level.

745
00:56:05,782 --> 00:56:08,368
It is out of control, Pete.

746
00:56:08,452 --> 00:56:12,497
I accepted it.
But not anymore. It is finished.

747
00:56:12,581 --> 00:56:15,501
Finished.
As of right now.

748
00:56:15,542 --> 00:56:18,670
I am your wife.
- I know.

749
00:56:18,754 --> 00:56:21,089
You remember that.

750
00:56:27,095 --> 00:56:29,264
Scott.
- Yeah.

751
00:56:31,850 --> 00:56:34,545
If Power tanks again,
I'm sending him down.

752
00:56:34,645 --> 00:56:37,589
You want me to tell him that?
- If you think he'll pitch better, yes.

753
00:56:37,689 --> 00:56:40,494
I wouldn't put money on this guy.

754
00:56:41,610 --> 00:56:44,245
Hey, take that for me, will ya?

755
00:56:46,823 --> 00:56:48,992
Pete Rose's office.

756
00:56:49,076 --> 00:56:51,311
Yeah, let me see if I can find him.

757
00:56:51,411 --> 00:56:54,039
Paul Janszen.

758
00:56:55,541 --> 00:56:58,944
He must have stepped out.
I'll let him know that you called.

759
00:56:59,044 --> 00:57:01,547
Yeah. OK.

760
00:57:04,758 --> 00:57:09,433
He says it's urgent
that you get back to him right away.

761
00:57:11,765 --> 00:57:13,767
Pete.

762
00:57:16,562 --> 00:57:18,130
Are you OK?

763
00:57:18,230 --> 00:57:22,217
Be careful with the friends you pick, Scott.
They can cause you a lot of problems. OK?

764
00:57:22,317 --> 00:57:24,736
Go play baseball.

765
00:57:24,778 --> 00:57:27,281
Go play baseball, come on.

766
00:57:39,293 --> 00:57:41,737
The number you have reached
is no longer in service...

767
00:57:41,837 --> 00:57:43,989
and there is no new number
at this time.

768
00:57:44,089 --> 00:57:46,216
This is a recording.

769
00:57:46,300 --> 00:57:50,805
The number you have reached
is no longer in service...

770
00:58:07,029 --> 00:58:10,259
FBI, Mr. Janszen.
Please open up.

771
00:58:20,292 --> 00:58:24,117
Mr. Janszen,
we're not gonna ask nicely again.

772
00:58:27,341 --> 00:58:29,635
Uh, just a second.

773
00:58:39,561 --> 00:58:42,381
Mr. Paul Janszen?
- You're Mr. Janszen, right?

774
00:58:42,481 --> 00:58:43,340
What's this about?

775
00:58:43,440 --> 00:58:45,843
You're under arrest
for the trafficking of illegal substances.

776
00:58:45,943 --> 00:58:49,768
Step back
and put your hands behind your head.

777
00:58:54,785 --> 00:58:56,395
You have the right to remain silent.

778
00:58:56,495 --> 00:58:59,022
Anything you say
can be used against you in a court of law.

779
00:58:59,122 --> 00:59:00,482
You have the right to an attorney.

780
00:59:00,582 --> 00:59:03,444
If you cannot afford an attorney,
one will be appointed to you by the court.

781
00:59:03,544 --> 00:59:07,781
Do you understand your rights
as I have read them to you?

782
00:59:07,881 --> 00:59:11,034
The most important thing
for you to keep in mind is this, Paul -...

783
00:59:11,134 --> 00:59:13,637
be honest, be forthright.

784
00:59:13,679 --> 00:59:17,416
Lying to us is only going to get you
deeper into what is already a bad situation.

785
00:59:17,516 --> 00:59:21,587
Perjury, added to narcotics trafficking,
you don't need.

786
00:59:21,687 --> 00:59:25,440
I have no idea what you're talking about.

787
00:59:26,191 --> 00:59:30,804
I mean, I've used steroids a few times
before, but, you know, who hasn't?

788
00:59:30,904 --> 00:59:33,098
I haven't.
I doubt my partner has.

789
00:59:33,198 --> 00:59:35,267
How 'bout your buddy Pete?

790
00:59:35,367 --> 00:59:37,352
Who?
- You know, Pete Rose.

791
00:59:37,452 --> 00:59:40,022
You two are, like, joined at the hip.

792
00:59:40,122 --> 00:59:43,609
I don't know anything about that.
- About what?

793
00:59:43,709 --> 00:59:46,737
Whatever it is
you're trying to get me to say.

794
00:59:46,837 --> 00:59:49,239
About anything.
- I'm a little confused.

795
00:59:49,339 --> 00:59:53,535
Are you trying to tell us Pete Rose
isn't involved in trafficking drugs with you?

796
00:59:53,635 --> 00:59:56,580
What?
- And Don Stenger and Tommy Gioiosa?

797
00:59:56,680 --> 01:00:00,918
Listen carefully, Paul.
You're with us or against us.

798
01:00:01,018 --> 01:00:03,353
No in-between.

799
01:00:23,957 --> 01:00:29,213
There's no more money.
I used what was left for bail.

800
01:00:29,254 --> 01:00:31,757
You're broke, Paul.

801
01:00:33,091 --> 01:00:35,828
How you gonna defend yourself, huh?

802
01:00:35,928 --> 01:00:38,430
How you gonna hire a lawyer?

803
01:00:40,432 --> 01:00:45,003
Pete will come through.
- He's the reason you're in this mess.

804
01:00:45,103 --> 01:00:48,524
When are you gonna admit that?

805
01:00:48,607 --> 01:00:52,361
He's not your friend, Paul,
he never was.

806
01:00:52,402 --> 01:00:58,033
He doesn't have friends.
You know, he has people that he uses.

807
01:00:58,116 --> 01:01:00,327
It was more than that.

808
01:01:01,370 --> 01:01:03,872
Then where is he now?

809
01:01:06,124 --> 01:01:07,860
I mean,
why doesn't he return your phone calls?

810
01:01:07,960 --> 01:01:09,361
Why doesn't he pay you back
your money?

811
01:01:09,461 --> 01:01:13,298
I told you a thousand times -...

812
01:01:13,382 --> 01:01:16,009
it's his wife.
It's Carol.

813
01:01:19,179 --> 01:01:24,293
If you want to keep fooling yourself,
then that's your business.

814
01:01:24,393 --> 01:01:26,895
I don't want any part of it.

815
01:01:31,316 --> 01:01:33,316
Katarina.

816
01:01:41,201 --> 01:01:43,954
There you go.
- Yeah.

817
01:01:44,037 --> 01:01:46,290
Perfect as always, Cathy.

818
01:01:46,373 --> 01:01:49,193
So, why don't you call me when
you get tired of that husband of yours?

819
01:01:49,293 --> 01:01:50,903
Oh, I've been tired of him for ten years.

820
01:01:51,003 --> 01:01:55,338
That doesn't mean
I need another bastard in my life.

821
01:02:03,932 --> 01:02:05,934
Hi, Pete.

822
01:02:08,437 --> 01:02:12,149
Hey, Paulie.
Where you been hiding yourself?

823
01:02:12,191 --> 01:02:14,943
Can we talk?
- Sure. Of course.

824
01:02:15,027 --> 01:02:20,115
But not right now.
I'm kinda in a rush. Got a game tonight.

825
01:02:20,199 --> 01:02:24,269
I'm in a lot of trouble, Pete.
- Yeah? What kind of trouble?

826
01:02:24,369 --> 01:02:27,773
I'm talking big trouble,
you know? Federal.

827
01:02:27,873 --> 01:02:30,709
It just happened.
I need a lawyer.

828
01:02:30,792 --> 01:02:35,005
I need money, Pete.
I need the money you owe me.

829
01:02:36,548 --> 01:02:39,885
Let's take this off the street.

830
01:02:47,601 --> 01:02:51,422
Why'd you freeze me out like that?
Was it just the money?

831
01:02:51,522 --> 01:02:55,347
You know me -
I don't give a shit about money.

832
01:02:56,068 --> 01:02:58,403
Maybe a little.

833
01:02:58,487 --> 01:03:01,056
Women, Paulie, they're like elephants.
They never forget.

834
01:03:01,156 --> 01:03:03,976
Carol's had a bug up her ass about you
ever since I almost got caught...

835
01:03:04,076 --> 01:03:05,894
testing the wrong oil.

836
01:03:05,994 --> 01:03:08,981
She knows I fool around - hell, I've been on
the road half my life, what do you expect? -...

837
01:03:09,081 --> 01:03:11,775
but every once in a while,
you know, she's got to put on a big show.

838
01:03:11,875 --> 01:03:17,239
Shove it down my throat. She's Mrs.
Pete Rose, not some floozy I'm banging.

839
01:03:17,339 --> 01:03:18,866
You just got caught in the middle,
that's all.

840
01:03:18,966 --> 01:03:21,618
I wish you would have
just been upfront with me all this time.

841
01:03:21,718 --> 01:03:24,388
I have been.
Carol's my wife.

842
01:03:24,471 --> 01:03:27,916
She's my wife. It's like they say -
a rock and a hard place.

843
01:03:28,016 --> 01:03:32,796
OK, but I just really need the money,
though. Can I have the money?

844
01:03:32,896 --> 01:03:36,592
How much you need?
- The full 30K. What you owe.

845
01:03:36,692 --> 01:03:39,497
Whoa.
That's a big number, Paulie.

846
01:03:39,570 --> 01:03:40,804
You figure it different?

847
01:03:40,904 --> 01:03:46,852
I'm just saying it's a whole lot of cash
to come up with, like, out of the blue.

848
01:03:46,952 --> 01:03:51,190
I'm not going to jail, Pete. And I don't want
anybody else to go to jail, either.

849
01:03:51,290 --> 01:03:53,584
OK.

850
01:03:53,625 --> 01:03:56,503
Come on, stop dancing.
Say it.

851
01:03:57,713 --> 01:04:01,623
OK. If I don't have a good lawyer,
I'm screwed.

852
01:04:02,759 --> 01:04:07,519
Now, I don't want to cooperate,
but if I have to, I will.

853
01:04:08,599 --> 01:04:10,934
Don't worry.

854
01:04:13,979 --> 01:04:17,841
Hey, go see Roger, my lawyer,
tomorrow afternoon. I'll set it up.

855
01:04:17,941 --> 01:04:21,511
I'll make sure
he takes care of everything.

856
01:04:22,654 --> 01:04:29,029
I knew I could count on you, Pete.
- Come on. Whose better than us, right?

857
01:04:35,459 --> 01:04:37,628
Thanks, buddy.

858
01:04:44,551 --> 01:04:47,413
Pete contacted me about your problem.

859
01:04:47,513 --> 01:04:51,208
He's always been a loyal friend and,
to be quite honest, against my advice...

860
01:04:51,308 --> 01:04:53,460
he's decided to help you out.

861
01:04:53,560 --> 01:04:58,273
Pete has a big heart, on and off the field.
Always has.

862
01:04:58,357 --> 01:05:01,176
I appreciate Pete's friendship,
but, uh,

863
01:05:01,276 --> 01:05:05,055
in all honesty,
this is money he borrowed from me.

864
01:05:05,155 --> 01:05:07,724
Excuse me for being so impertinent,
but why on earth...

865
01:05:07,824 --> 01:05:12,479
would my client need to borrow money
from you or anyone else, for that matter?

866
01:05:12,579 --> 01:05:19,124
I don't think we should get into that.
- Please, you've piqued my curiosity.

867
01:05:19,211 --> 01:05:22,072
Your client
has a major gambling problem.

868
01:05:22,172 --> 01:05:27,261
Is that so? And how do you come by
such intimate knowledge?

869
01:05:27,344 --> 01:05:30,064
I'm the guy who placed his bets.

870
01:05:35,894 --> 01:05:38,046
What's this?
- Pure generosity.

871
01:05:38,146 --> 01:05:40,549
My client has assured me
he doesn't owe you a penny,

872
01:05:40,649 --> 01:05:44,729
but he's agreed to loan you
ten thousand dollars.

873
01:05:45,612 --> 01:05:48,927
He's gonna loan me
ten thousand dollars?

874
01:05:48,991 --> 01:05:52,661
That sick bastard owes me 30 grand.

875
01:05:53,245 --> 01:05:58,750
30 thousand dollars.
Do you understand me, you little prick?

876
01:05:59,209 --> 01:06:02,354
Your client is a gambling degenerate.

877
01:06:02,421 --> 01:06:05,491
He bets on his own sport,
that's how sick he is.

878
01:06:05,591 --> 01:06:08,141
Please, Mr. Janszen, sit down.

879
01:06:09,386 --> 01:06:11,386
OK.

880
01:06:18,228 --> 01:06:21,148
What happened?
What's wrong? Paul?

881
01:06:21,231 --> 01:06:26,416
That son of a bitch
just made the biggest mistake of his life.

882
01:07:16,119 --> 01:07:17,438
Pete.

883
01:07:17,538 --> 01:07:19,538
Carol.

884
01:07:27,506 --> 01:07:29,506
Pete.

885
01:08:11,049 --> 01:08:14,078
You can't just waltz into people's houses
and take things.

886
01:08:14,178 --> 01:08:16,371
There's a law against that.
It's called 'breaking and entering. '

887
01:08:16,471 --> 01:08:20,334
Like I said before, I used my key.
Pete gave it to me a long time ago.

888
01:08:20,434 --> 01:08:22,294
So what's this?
- His betting sheets.

889
01:08:22,394 --> 01:08:26,465
We don't give a damn about gambling.
We told you that. This is about narcotics.

890
01:08:26,565 --> 01:08:29,635
The R stands for 'Reds. '
- He bet on his own team?

891
01:08:29,735 --> 01:08:32,387
For years, and big.
'2' is for two grand.

892
01:08:32,487 --> 01:08:34,765
Well, that's a major league
baseball problem, not yours.

893
01:08:34,865 --> 01:08:41,495
Your problems, Paul, are why we're here,
and what you should be worrying about.

894
01:08:59,598 --> 01:09:01,166
So?

895
01:09:01,266 --> 01:09:02,960
So I wanted you to know...

896
01:09:03,060 --> 01:09:07,965
that all that shit about me placing bets
in Pete's name was a lie.

897
01:09:08,065 --> 01:09:09,967
I mean, every bet was his.

898
01:09:10,067 --> 01:09:12,957
My mother didn't raise any morons.

899
01:09:13,403 --> 01:09:17,398
Did he ever make good?
- The bat. I got the bat.

900
01:09:17,449 --> 01:09:19,726
The one he broke Cobb's record with.

901
01:09:19,826 --> 01:09:22,187
I hate to tell you,
but there's a lot of them around.

902
01:09:22,287 --> 01:09:28,318
The jerk I sold it to don't know that.
What's the point of this little get-together?

903
01:09:28,418 --> 01:09:33,688
I wanted to know if you'd be interested
in some other business.

904
01:09:34,091 --> 01:09:38,136
Something very profitable.
- Get to the point.

905
01:09:39,805 --> 01:09:43,000
I got a source
get me all the steroids I want.

906
01:09:43,100 --> 01:09:46,545
If the price is right,
I could be interested.

907
01:09:46,645 --> 01:09:49,439
I was hoping you'd say that.

908
01:09:51,400 --> 01:09:54,205
You like living, don't you, Paul?

909
01:10:11,128 --> 01:10:13,255
Look into my eyes.

910
01:10:17,176 --> 01:10:19,981
That's right.
There's nobody home.

911
01:10:24,349 --> 01:10:26,685
Yeah, yeah.
OK. Bye.

912
01:10:38,447 --> 01:10:41,433
Yeah, hello.
- Mikey. You there?

913
01:10:41,533 --> 01:10:43,268
I ain't on the moon.

914
01:10:43,368 --> 01:10:48,457
I just wanted to warn you.
Get ready to duck.

915
01:10:49,249 --> 01:10:50,943
What the hell are you talking about?

916
01:10:51,043 --> 01:10:56,156
I always liked you, and that's
the only reason that I'm making this call.

917
01:10:56,256 --> 01:11:00,661
Just... Just trust me here.
The shit's gonna hit the fan.

918
01:11:00,761 --> 01:11:04,331
Hey, Paulie, I don't like this kinda talk.

919
01:11:05,682 --> 01:11:08,502
Consider yourself lucky we're having it.

920
01:11:08,602 --> 01:11:11,230
Paulie.
Paulie, listen to me...

921
01:11:34,837 --> 01:11:36,964
Wanna get that?

922
01:11:37,047 --> 01:11:39,047
Nope.

923
01:11:42,761 --> 01:11:46,586
Please leave
a message after the beep. Thanks.

924
01:11:46,682 --> 01:11:48,375
What the hell's going on, Paulie?

