01:11:48,475 --> 01:11:52,504
I just talked to Mike. What's all this'Get
ready to duck'crap you're talking about?

926
01:11:52,604 --> 01:11:55,340
I really hope you're not doing
something you're gonna regret.

927
01:11:55,440 --> 01:11:57,901
Call me back right away.

928
01:11:57,985 --> 01:12:00,320
He sounds panicked.

929
01:12:03,782 --> 01:12:05,868
You OK?

930
01:12:05,951 --> 01:12:07,951
Yeah.

931
01:12:08,996 --> 01:12:11,248
It feels good -...

932
01:12:11,290 --> 01:12:13,750
not fooling myself anymore.

933
01:12:23,427 --> 01:12:26,346
Is your name Paul Janszen?
- Yes.

934
01:12:26,430 --> 01:12:29,249
Were you once employed
at the Queen City Barrel Company?

935
01:12:29,349 --> 01:12:30,375
Yes.

936
01:12:30,475 --> 01:12:33,437
Are you still employed there?

937
01:12:33,520 --> 01:12:35,172
No.

938
01:12:35,272 --> 01:12:37,508
Have you ever sold
or knowingly associated...

939
01:12:37,608 --> 01:12:40,694
with people who sold illegal drugs?

940
01:12:44,406 --> 01:12:46,183
Yes.

941
01:12:46,283 --> 01:12:50,078
Did you ever sell drugs to Pete Rose?

942
01:12:50,162 --> 01:12:52,206
No.

943
01:12:52,247 --> 01:12:57,444
Did Pete Rose ever knowingly associate
with people who sold illegal drugs?

944
01:12:57,544 --> 01:12:59,279
Yes.

945
01:12:59,379 --> 01:13:04,076
Was Pete Rose aware
that you yourself had dealt illegal drugs?

946
01:13:04,176 --> 01:13:05,702
Yes.

947
01:13:05,802 --> 01:13:09,873
Did Pete Rose ever bet
on the Cincinnati Reds baseball team?

948
01:13:09,973 --> 01:13:11,973
Yes.

949
01:13:12,100 --> 01:13:18,220
Did you yourself place bets for Pete Rose
on major league baseball games?

950
01:13:21,026 --> 01:13:23,026
Yes.

951
01:13:33,330 --> 01:13:36,400
Major League Baseball.
Mr. Ueberroth's office.

952
01:13:36,500 --> 01:13:40,237
No, I'm sorry.
Mr. Ueberroth is in a meeting right now.

953
01:13:40,337 --> 01:13:42,197
OK. I will.

954
01:13:42,297 --> 01:13:44,297
Thank you. Bye.

955
01:13:52,474 --> 01:13:55,627
How long we supposed to wait, huh?
What's this? An audience with the Pope?

956
01:13:55,727 --> 01:13:58,505
He's the damned baseball commissioner,
not the president.

957
01:13:58,605 --> 01:14:00,649
Pete, listen to me.

958
01:14:00,732 --> 01:14:04,636
The commissioner didn't call you up here
to waste your time. This is serious.

959
01:14:04,736 --> 01:14:08,532
Yeah.
I'm serious, too.

960
01:14:08,615 --> 01:14:10,267
Peter.
- Hello, Pete. How are you?

961
01:14:10,367 --> 01:14:13,479
Nice bunch of pictures on the wall outside.
Why aren't I up there?

962
01:14:13,579 --> 01:14:17,024
This is Ed Durso, our chief operating
officer and long time counsel.

963
01:14:17,124 --> 01:14:18,192
You know Fay, of course.
- Hi.

964
01:14:18,292 --> 01:14:19,777
And Bart Giamatti,
our commissioner elect.

965
01:14:19,877 --> 01:14:21,737
How are you?
- Congratulations. Better you than me.

966
01:14:21,837 --> 01:14:23,322
I got my hands full
just running the team.

967
01:14:23,422 --> 01:14:24,907
Glad you could make it
on such short notice.

968
01:14:25,007 --> 01:14:26,283
Well, I hate to leave my guys, but...

969
01:14:26,383 --> 01:14:28,202
Well, we appreciate it, Pete.
All of us.

970
01:14:28,302 --> 01:14:33,290
This shouldn't take long.
- I got a short attention span, I hope not.

971
01:14:33,390 --> 01:14:35,751
All right, Pete. What we need,
the reason we asked you in today...

972
01:14:35,851 --> 01:14:38,337
concerns the allegations
about your gambling.

973
01:14:38,437 --> 01:14:41,412
I'll lay five to one it's all bull.

974
01:14:42,649 --> 01:14:48,388
Well, we heard that Sports Illustrated
is about to run a rather unflattering story.

975
01:14:48,488 --> 01:14:51,850
Which contains nothing
but utter false accusations.

976
01:14:51,950 --> 01:14:53,852
I don't doubt it.
And one of the sources, Paul Janszen,

977
01:14:53,952 --> 01:14:55,938
is rather disreputable,
to put it mildly.

978
01:14:56,038 --> 01:14:59,566
He's a flat-out liar.
- I don't doubt that's true.

979
01:14:59,666 --> 01:15:03,779
Well, Pete, how would you describe
your relationship with Mr. Janszen?

980
01:15:03,879 --> 01:15:09,076
Relationship? There was none. He was a...
How would you say? A gofer.

981
01:15:09,176 --> 01:15:11,203
He ran errands.
You know how it is with these guys -...

982
01:15:11,303 --> 01:15:13,956
you're nice to 'em, then they start to
imagine they're your best friend and then...

983
01:15:14,056 --> 01:15:17,167
You know: Don't get too close to the help.
- Exactly.

984
01:15:17,267 --> 01:15:19,920
It was my big heart
landed me in the shitter.

985
01:15:20,020 --> 01:15:24,508
So we can take it that the allegations
you bet on baseball are entirely false?

986
01:15:24,608 --> 01:15:27,903
Commissioner, never.

987
01:15:27,986 --> 01:15:30,614
Not once in my life.

988
01:15:30,697 --> 01:15:32,824
I'd have to be insane.

989
01:15:32,908 --> 01:15:38,814
I'd have to be the dumbest son of a bitch
in the whole world to do that.

990
01:15:38,914 --> 01:15:44,361
Well, nothing could be more damaging
to the fabric of our national pastime...

991
01:15:44,461 --> 01:15:46,461
than illicit gambling.

992
01:15:46,463 --> 01:15:50,617
I agree with you 110 per cent, Bart, which
is why I don't bet on baseball, gentlemen,

993
01:15:50,717 --> 01:15:53,428
and I never will.

994
01:15:53,846 --> 01:15:57,374
But you do go to the track quite often,
that's fair to say, isn't it?

995
01:15:57,474 --> 01:15:59,251
When I was about this big, Fay,

996
01:15:59,351 --> 01:16:02,045
my dad used to take me to the track
for the sport of it.

997
01:16:02,145 --> 01:16:04,355
He couldn't afford to bet.

998
01:16:04,356 --> 01:16:09,319
Now I take my son,
and one day my son will take his son.

999
01:16:09,361 --> 01:16:11,996
And that doesn't mean it's bad.

1000
01:16:12,114 --> 01:16:16,743
Guys, if it was bad,
I just wouldn't do it.

1001
01:16:21,290 --> 01:16:24,193
Well, Pete,
we just thought it best to clear the air.

1002
01:16:24,293 --> 01:16:26,278
We'll call you
if we have any other questions.

1003
01:16:26,378 --> 01:16:29,406
OK. We all got enough to do without
worrying about what some moron says.

1004
01:16:29,506 --> 01:16:30,491
Right, Peter?
- Right.

1005
01:16:30,591 --> 01:16:34,011
OK. Thank you.
Bart. Fay, Ed.

1006
01:16:34,094 --> 01:16:38,415
Oh, don't forget about my picture, OK?
- Bye, gentlemen.

1007
01:16:38,515 --> 01:16:40,584
So long, Pete.
- So, what do you think?

1008
01:16:40,684 --> 01:16:43,295
Like he said, he'd have to be insane.
I believe him.

1009
01:16:43,395 --> 01:16:45,547
I do, too, actually.
- I don't disagree.

1010
01:16:45,647 --> 01:16:48,717
But as long as you have these accusations
with such gravity...

1011
01:16:48,817 --> 01:16:51,320
Yeah.
That article.

1012
01:16:51,403 --> 01:16:53,722
It's gonna create a certain climate.
- Right.

1013
01:16:53,822 --> 01:16:56,683
Maybe it's time to bring in John Dowd.
- Do you think he's the right guy?

1014
01:16:56,783 --> 01:17:01,730
Well, he prosecuted the Mob for the
Justice Department. I think it's a good idea.

1015
01:17:01,830 --> 01:17:04,316
Mr. Dowd. A pleasure to meet you, sir.
- And you.

1016
01:17:04,416 --> 01:17:06,710
My associate.

1017
01:17:08,504 --> 01:17:12,116
Materials I've gathered
from Janszen on Rose.

1018
01:17:12,216 --> 01:17:14,676
Checks signed by Rose.

1019
01:17:20,516 --> 01:17:23,236
Hello, Ron.
Thanks for coming in.

1020
01:17:32,778 --> 01:17:36,181
Pete, did anyone in association with you
bet on baseball...

1021
01:17:36,281 --> 01:17:40,477
or talk about betting on baseball
between 1985 and 1987?

1022
01:17:40,577 --> 01:17:42,563
I don't know what you mean,
'talk about betting on baseball, '...

1023
01:17:42,663 --> 01:17:45,553
but no one bet baseball around me.

1024
01:17:45,999 --> 01:17:49,194
Pete, you previously testified
that you did no gambling business...

1025
01:17:49,294 --> 01:17:51,405
with anyone
other than Janszen at the track.

1026
01:17:51,505 --> 01:17:54,883
That's correct.
- All right.

1027
01:17:54,925 --> 01:18:00,806
Pete, the Reds played Atlanta
on April 28, 1987. A 7:35 game.

1028
01:18:01,431 --> 01:18:04,752
Phone records show Paul Janszen
called Ron Delaplane that same day...

1029
01:18:04,852 --> 01:18:08,188
at 5:59, 6:16 and 6:43,

1030
01:18:08,272 --> 01:18:13,032
then called the Reds clubhouse
at 6:45 and again at 6:55.

1031
01:18:14,194 --> 01:18:16,780
He called five times?
Hm.

1032
01:18:16,864 --> 01:18:19,558
Do you know what that telephone traffic
is all about?

1033
01:18:19,658 --> 01:18:21,869
No. No idea.

1034
01:18:21,952 --> 01:18:24,938
You're aware that Paul Janszen
has testified that he bet on baseball?

1035
01:18:25,038 --> 01:18:27,316
Bet on the Cincinnati Reds for you?

1036
01:18:27,416 --> 01:18:30,402
I'm sure he probably did,
from reading the trouble he's in.

1037
01:18:30,502 --> 01:18:33,781
You know,
people have a tendency to say things...

1038
01:18:33,881 --> 01:18:36,200
when their ass is on the chopping block.

1039
01:18:36,300 --> 01:18:38,619
Perhaps we should take a break.

1040
01:18:38,719 --> 01:18:41,330
My client's been answering questions
for hours.

1041
01:18:41,430 --> 01:18:44,850
I'm OK.
I'm fine.

1042
01:18:44,933 --> 01:18:47,377
I just want to get it over with.

1043
01:18:47,477 --> 01:18:50,923
Pete, what if I were to tell you that we have
physical evidence that directly links you...

1044
01:18:51,023 --> 01:18:53,258
to numerous wagers
placed over a period of months...

1045
01:18:53,358 --> 01:18:56,261
on football, basketball,
hockey and baseball games?

1046
01:18:56,361 --> 01:18:57,805
I...

1047
01:18:57,905 --> 01:18:59,515
I might have...

1048
01:18:59,615 --> 01:19:02,768
I might have bet
the occasional football game,

1049
01:19:02,868 --> 01:19:07,831
but never in my life
did I bet on baseball.

1050
01:19:08,207 --> 01:19:11,437
Never bet on baseball?
- Never. Ever.

1051
01:19:14,922 --> 01:19:16,922
Not once.

1052
01:19:18,675 --> 01:19:22,621
Pete, we have phone records
of Paul Janszen, Mike Bertolini,

1053
01:19:22,721 --> 01:19:25,666
calls placed from your home phone,
from the Reds' clubhouse,

1054
01:19:25,766 --> 01:19:28,752
betting slips with your handwriting on 'em,
numerous canceled checks.

1055
01:19:28,852 --> 01:19:31,657
I'm gonna say this one more time.

1056
01:19:34,691 --> 01:19:40,864
I never bet on baseball...

1057
01:19:40,906 --> 01:19:43,367
in my whole life.

1058
01:19:43,408 --> 01:19:46,553
Not from the clubhouse,
from New York,

1059
01:19:46,578 --> 01:19:49,064
from New England,
from New Mexico.

1060
01:19:49,164 --> 01:19:51,291
From nowhere.

1061
01:19:57,047 --> 01:19:59,491
If I'm guilty of anything
in this whole mess,

1062
01:19:59,591 --> 01:20:06,265
it's from being
a horseshit selector of friends.

1063
01:20:22,030 --> 01:20:24,030
It's all there.

1064
01:20:24,700 --> 01:20:28,312
Is there any doubt in your mind
that Rose bet on baseball?

1065
01:20:28,412 --> 01:20:31,123
None whatsoever.

1066
01:20:41,550 --> 01:20:44,511
How'd it go?
- What are those?

1067
01:20:44,553 --> 01:20:47,164
Flowers.
- Well, I know that much.

1068
01:20:47,264 --> 01:20:49,808
Azaleas.
Beautiful, huh?

1069
01:20:49,892 --> 01:20:52,853
Strong and tenacious.

1070
01:20:52,936 --> 01:20:56,632
Roger's still in the dark.
You'd think after all these months,

1071
01:20:56,732 --> 01:20:59,301
Giamatti'd be just as anxious as me
to bury this whole mess.

1072
01:20:59,401 --> 01:21:02,971
I mean, what are they waiting for, Carol,
huh? For me to become an old man?

1073
01:21:03,071 --> 01:21:06,934
You are an old man.
- Watch out. I'll prove you wrong.

1074
01:21:07,034 --> 01:21:07,976
Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1075
01:21:08,076 --> 01:21:09,812
There's a reason
they call me Charlie Hustle, you know.

1076
01:21:09,912 --> 01:21:12,789
I heard a rumor about that once.

1077
01:21:16,126 --> 01:21:18,487
When this whole mess is over,

1078
01:21:18,587 --> 01:21:21,052
we should take a trip, honey.

1079
01:21:21,840 --> 01:21:23,840
Europe, maybe.

1080
01:21:24,176 --> 01:21:27,704
How about Japan?
They like baseball in Japan.

1081
01:21:27,804 --> 01:21:32,768
Give them a chance
to meet a real baseball hero.

1082
01:21:47,074 --> 01:21:49,309
OK, Bart.
I got it. I understand.

1083
01:21:49,409 --> 01:21:53,605
We're in sync.
I'll talk to Pete and we'll get back later.

1084
01:21:53,705 --> 01:21:56,083
Come on, already.
Come on.

1085
01:21:56,166 --> 01:22:00,963
OK. Listen carefully
because this is the best we can do.

1086
01:22:01,046 --> 01:22:04,116
According to the agreement,
you will be banned from baseball,

1087
01:22:04,216 --> 01:22:06,702
reviewable after one year.
Please, both of you, hear me out.

1088
01:22:06,802 --> 01:22:09,246
Yeah, OK. What about
the betting on baseball stuff? I mean...

1089
01:22:09,346 --> 01:22:12,124
There'll be no finding.
- W-What's that mean?

1090
01:22:12,224 --> 01:22:14,710
Giamatti said MLB
won't rule one way or another.

1091
01:22:14,810 --> 01:22:17,254
It's a dead issue.
They won't bring it up.

1092
01:22:17,354 --> 01:22:21,216
The ban is for gambling on other sports,
not on baseball.

1093
01:22:21,316 --> 01:22:22,760
Over and out.
- Banned?

1094
01:22:22,860 --> 01:22:26,555
Again, it's reviewable after one year.
Then Pete gets another shot.

1095
01:22:26,655 --> 01:22:30,392
And the league can never say
you bet on baseball. Never.

1096
01:22:30,492 --> 01:22:35,147
Pete, this has been
a complete public-relations nightmare.

1097
01:22:35,247 --> 01:22:38,484
You're not happy.
Believe me, Giamatti's not happy, either.

1098
01:22:38,584 --> 01:22:40,879
He wanted to make his case.

1099
01:22:40,919 --> 01:22:44,406
We've done everything.
Blocked 'em in court, subpoenaed them.

1100
01:22:44,506 --> 01:22:49,181
Now this is their final offer.
We've run out of options.

1101
01:23:01,857 --> 01:23:06,486
The banishment for life
of Pete Rose from baseball...

1102
01:23:06,570 --> 01:23:09,573
is the sad end of a sorry episode.

1103
01:23:10,115 --> 01:23:14,728
One of the game's greatest players
has engaged in a variety of acts,

1104
01:23:14,828 --> 01:23:16,980
which have stained the game,

1105
01:23:17,080 --> 01:23:21,235
and he now must live
with the consequences of those acts.

1106
01:23:21,335 --> 01:23:23,862
He's gonna have to
face some consequences, too.

1107
01:23:23,962 --> 01:23:26,465
No player or manager,

1108
01:23:27,132 --> 01:23:31,261
no matter how exalted,
is above the game.

1109
01:23:31,345 --> 01:23:34,623
The integrity of baseball itself
is at stake.

1110
01:23:34,723 --> 01:23:37,668
The matter of Mr. Rose is now closed.

1111
01:23:37,768 --> 01:23:39,378
Commissioner.

1112
01:23:39,478 --> 01:23:42,878
Did Pete Rose
bet on baseball?

1113
01:23:42,940 --> 01:23:45,943
In my opinion - yes.

1114
01:23:46,944 --> 01:23:49,494
Pete Rose did bet on baseball.

1115
01:23:49,905 --> 01:23:51,990
What?
- That bastard.

1116
01:23:52,074 --> 01:23:54,143
He went against the agreement.

1117
01:23:54,243 --> 01:23:57,271
Theirs was no finding. No finding
as to whether he ever bet on baseball.

1118
01:23:57,371 --> 01:24:02,584
They screwed us.
- You know what, Rog? Screw 'em.

1119
01:24:02,626 --> 01:24:05,941
I'll have the last word if it kills me.

1120
01:24:07,965 --> 01:24:10,467
I'll have the last word.

1121
01:24:30,571 --> 01:24:33,849
Trust me on this.
I'll be out of baseball a very short time.

1122
01:24:33,949 --> 01:24:35,949
Pete.
Over here.

1123
01:24:35,993 --> 01:24:39,396
Pete, were you surprised
by Commissioner Giamatti's statement?

1124
01:24:39,496 --> 01:24:45,956
I was a little surprised by some of
those remarks. Some, I didn't understand.

1125
01:24:47,004 --> 01:24:49,573
What are you gonna do
with yourself, Pete?

1126
01:24:49,673 --> 01:24:51,075
Nothing.

1127
01:24:51,175 --> 01:24:57,890
L'll have to do without baseball for
the first time since I was seven years old.

1128
01:24:58,056 --> 01:24:59,875
Pete.

1129
01:24:59,975 --> 01:25:02,461
Hey, you know what they can't
take away from me?

1130
01:25:02,561 --> 01:25:04,646
From the fans?

1131
01:25:05,105 --> 01:25:09,468
The bits and pieces of myself
I left behind in all those ballparks...

1132
01:25:09,568 --> 01:25:13,071
for 27 years.
- Pete.

1133
01:25:13,155 --> 01:25:17,810
They can't... They can't have that.
- Pete. Pete, over here.

1134
01:25:17,910 --> 01:25:21,395
If the Commissioner... Pete?
- Pete. Pete.

1135
01:25:21,455 --> 01:25:23,107
Did you ever bet on baseball, Pete?

1136
01:25:23,207 --> 01:25:25,692
Well, regardless of what
the Commissioner said today,

1137
01:25:25,792 --> 01:25:28,257
I never bet on baseball.
Um...

1138
01:25:36,386 --> 01:25:39,956
That's all I can say.
- Pete.

1139
01:25:48,815 --> 01:25:51,135
Pete, hi.
- Just one more question.

1140
01:25:51,235 --> 01:25:54,112
Over here.
Over here.

1141
01:25:58,617 --> 01:26:00,617
It's OK, Pete.

1142
01:27:13,400 --> 01:27:16,205
There's a high drive, way back...

1143
01:27:21,283 --> 01:27:24,745
Pete Rose.
He's circling the bases.

1144
01:27:29,750 --> 01:27:32,085
Holy cow.

1145
01:27:32,169 --> 01:27:35,005
What a thrill to watch him.

1146
01:27:35,088 --> 01:27:38,403
The crowd giving him
a standing ovation.

1147
01:28:06,411 --> 01:28:11,341
You have always denied,
publicly, that you bet on baseball.

1148
01:28:11,708 --> 01:28:13,836
Did you bet on baseball?

1149
01:28:15,879 --> 01:28:19,633
Yes, I did. And that was my mistake.

1150
01:28:20,259 --> 01:28:23,136
Did you bet on your own team?

1151
01:28:23,220 --> 01:28:25,220
Yes.

